  "text": "An analogical algometer (Wagner, FDK 20) was used to investigate the pressure-pain threshold (PPT) before and after computer work. The PPT describes the amount of pressure needed for the first sensation of pain. Each subject was asked to say \"stop\" when his sensation changed from pressure to pain [CITATION_1] . The PPT was measured 2 cm lateral to the location of the upper trapezius EMG attachment site.",
